Class EllipseAnnotation

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pepstock.charba.client.commons.NativeObjectContainer
      • org.pepstock.charba.client.commons.AbstractNode
        • org.pepstock.charba.client.annotation.AbstractAnnotation
          • org.pepstock.charba.client.annotation.AbstractXYAnnotation
            • org.pepstock.charba.client.annotation.EllipseAnnotation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HasBackgroundColor, IsDefaultsAnnotation, IsDefaultsBackgroundColorHandler, IsDefaultsEllipseAnnotation, IsDefaultsXYAnnotation

    public final class EllipseAnnotation
extends AbstractXYAnnotation
implements IsDefaultsEllipseAnnotation, HasBackgroundColor
    Implements a ELLIPSE annotation which draws a ellipse in the a chart.
    If one of the axes is not specified, the ellipse will take the entire chart dimension.
    The 4 coordinates, xMin, xMax, yMin, yMax are optional. If not specified, the ellipse is expanded out to the edges.
    Author:
    Andrea "Stock" Stocchero
